         Give multiclassing with max of a level 20 in another class, but takes same xp to reach 20 in it as it does 60 in your own.  This would only come after dinging 60.</P><P><BR>IE: I ding 60 then begin work on multiclassing as a cleric.  5 yellow bubs of xp later, I can cast level 1 cleric spells.</P><P>You certainly wouldn't want a warlock casting complete heal.  Hell.  Why would anyone play anything else warriors multiclassed as clerics?  So I think the cutoff level would be level 20 spells.  Once you ding 20 as a cleric, you are still a 60 necro but can scribe up to level 19 cleric spells.  Maybe then you'd go for wizard ... :p</P><P><BR>On second thought.. this is overpowering.  But some limited form of multiclassing (ie huge time sink in order to give warriors the ability to feign death) would be neat.</P><P>I guess they already give this to a limited degree with our 59+ Class Abilities.</P><P></P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
