         My only major complaint is the 3d engine.  It's archaic and painful.  All they need to do is introduce some code so that the engine will NOT draw polgons that are not immediately visible, and we'd see performance improvements like you couldn't possibly imagine!</P><P>Good example.  When you zone into the bazaar from shadowhaven, try looking out toward the vendor stalls.  You go down to around 2-5 frames/sec even though you are looking at a SOLID WALL!  As soon as you look the other way your framerate goes back up.  If they could fix this problem it would soooo much improve the game.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
